# Accepted upstream advisories — see SECURITY.md for the full rationale.
# Each entry should be revisited on every dependency review.

# nodemailer 7.x — SMTP command injection via envelope.size + CRLF in name.
# We never expose these fields to user input; reassess when @auth/core pins
# a patched version.
CVE-2024-39008
CVE-2025-XXX  # placeholder for the second nodemailer advisory once it has a CVE

# postcss < 8.5.10 — XSS via unescaped </style> in CSS stringify. Build-time
# only against our own CSS files. No fix without downgrading Next major.
CVE-2024-XXX  # placeholder

# @hono/node-server < 1.19.13 — middleware bypass via repeated slashes.
# Transitive via @prisma/dev which we don't invoke.
CVE-2024-XXX  # placeholder
